# Databricks Runtime & Photon

## Databricks Runtime (DBR)

Every cluster boots a **DBR** — a pre-built image of tuned Apache Spark plus Delta Lake, optimized libraries, and the OS. Releases are **versioned** (e.g. DBR 15.x), so environments are reproducible.

- Prefer an **LTS (long-term support)** version for production stability
- The **ML runtime** variant adds machine-learning libraries and GPU support

## Photon — the C++ query engine

Databricks' **vectorized** engine, a drop-in replacement for Spark's that accelerates **SQL and DataFrame** work — the same query runs faster and usually cheaper. **Transparent to your code:** enable it and eligible operations run on the native engine — no rewrite.
